---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import AdSlot from '../../components/AdSlot.astro';
import siteConfig from '../../data/site-config.json';
import blogPosts from '../../data/blog-posts.json';

const post = blogPosts.find(p => p.slug === 'portable-restroom-industry-trends-2025')!;
const siteUrl = `https://${siteConfig.domain}`;

const articleData = {
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  datePublished: post.publishedAt,
  dateModified: post.updatedAt,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: post.author.name,
    description: post.author.bio
  },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: siteConfig.name,
    logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: `${siteUrl}/images/PottyDirectory_Logo.png` }
  },
  mainEntityOfPage: { '@type': 'WebPage', '@id': `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}` }
};

const relatedPosts = blogPosts.filter(p => p.slug !== post.slug).slice(0, 3);
---

<BaseLayout title={post.title} description={post.description}>
  <StructuredData type="Article" data={articleData} />

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <nav class="mb-8">
      <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-primary-600">Home</a></li>
        <li>/</li>
        <li><a href="/blog" class="hover:text-primary-600">Blog</a></li>
        <li>/</li>
        <li class="text-gray-900">2025 Industry Trends</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-10">
      <span class="inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full mb-4">Industry</span>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">{post.description}</p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-primary-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mr-3">
            <span class="text-primary-600 font-bold text-lg">PP</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-medium text-gray-900">{post.author.name}</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">{post.readTime} â€¢ Updated December 2024</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

      <p>
        The portable restroom industry is experiencing significant changes in 2025. From new technologies and sustainability initiatives to supply chain challenges and shifting consumer expectations, here's what's shaping the market this year.
      </p>

      <AdSlot slot="content" />

      <h2 id="market-growth">Market Size and Growth</h2>

      <p>
        The global portable toilet rental market is valued at approximately <strong>$24.7 billion in 2025</strong>, with projections reaching $50.4 billion by 2035. This represents a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 7.4%.
      </p>

      <h3>Key Growth Drivers</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Construction boom:</strong> Infrastructure investments and housing demand continue to drive the largest market segment (55% of rentals)</li>
        <li><strong>Event industry recovery:</strong> Post-pandemic surge in outdoor events, festivals, and gatherings</li>
        <li><strong>Heightened hygiene awareness:</strong> Lasting behavioral changes from COVID-19</li>
        <li><strong>Luxury segment expansion:</strong> Growing demand for upscale restroom trailers at weddings and corporate events</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 my-8">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900">By the Numbers</p>
        <p class="text-blue-800 mt-2">The luxury portable restroom segment is growing at 8.6% annually - faster than the overall market - as event planners and couples increasingly invest in guest experience.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="pricing-changes">Pricing Changes in 2025</h2>

      <h3>What's Driving Price Increases</h3>

      <p>Several factors are pushing rental prices higher in 2025:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Tariffs on imported materials:</strong> New import tariffs have increased manufacturing costs for plastic components and accessories</li>
        <li><strong>Fuel costs:</strong> Delivery and servicing costs remain elevated</li>
        <li><strong>Labor market:</strong> Driver and service technician wages have increased significantly</li>
        <li><strong>Demand pressure:</strong> Strong event and construction demand is creating supply constraints</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Current Pricing Trends</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Standard units:</strong> 10-15% higher than 2024 in many markets</li>
        <li><strong>Last-minute bookings:</strong> Premium charges of 30-45% for rush requests</li>
        <li><strong>Peak season surcharges:</strong> More common and higher than previous years</li>
        <li><strong>Delivery fees:</strong> Increasing as fuel and labor costs rise</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="booking-lead-times">Extended Booking Lead Times</h2>

      <p>
        One of the biggest changes in 2025 is how far ahead you need to book:
      </p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
        <table class="min-w-full border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <thead class="bg-gray-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Rental Type</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">Previous Lead Time</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900">2025 Recommendation</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-900">Standard Event</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">1-2 weeks</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">3-4 weeks</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-900">Large Event (500+)</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">1 month</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">2-3 months</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-900">Luxury Trailers</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">2-3 months</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">3-4 months</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-900">Specialty Units</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">3-4 weeks</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">6-8 weeks</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <AdSlot slot="content" />

      <h2 id="technology">Technology Innovations</h2>

      <h3>Smart Features Becoming Standard</h3>

      <p>Even basic units are getting technology upgrades:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Improved LED lighting:</strong> Solar-charged interior lights are now common on standard units</li>
        <li><strong>Better ventilation systems:</strong> Advanced airflow designs reduce odors significantly</li>
        <li><strong>Hands-free flushing:</strong> Foot-pedal and sensor-activated flush mechanisms</li>
        <li><strong>Occupancy indicators:</strong> External lights showing availability</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Digital Integration</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>QR code reporting:</strong> Users can report cleanliness issues directly to service providers</li>
        <li><strong>GPS tracking:</strong> Real-time location monitoring for delivery and pickup</li>
        <li><strong>IoT sensors:</strong> Tank level monitoring for optimized servicing schedules</li>
        <li><strong>Online booking:</strong> More companies offering instant quotes and reservations</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="sustainability">Sustainability Focus</h2>

      <p>
        Environmental consciousness is reshaping the industry. According to industry surveys, <strong>64% of consumers prefer eco-friendly options</strong> when available.
      </p>

      <h3>Green Innovations</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Solar-powered units:</strong> Rooftop panels power lights, fans, and pumps without generators</li>
        <li><strong>Biodegradable chemicals:</strong> Industry moving away from formaldehyde-based deodorizers</li>
        <li><strong>Recycled materials:</strong> Manufacturers using recycled plastics in unit construction</li>
        <li><strong>Water-saving features:</strong> Low-flush and waterless urinal options</li>
        <li><strong>Electric service vehicles:</strong> Some companies transitioning fleets to reduce emissions</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Composting Toilets</h3>

      <p>
        Waterless composting units are gaining traction for eco-conscious events and remote locations. While not suitable for all applications, they eliminate the need for water and chemical additives.
      </p>

      <h2 id="hygiene-features">Enhanced Hygiene Features</h2>

      <p>Post-pandemic expectations have permanently raised the bar for sanitation:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Antimicrobial surfaces:</strong> Treatments lasting up to 30 days between applications</li>
        <li><strong>Touchless everything:</strong> Doors, faucets, soap dispensers, and paper towel dispensers</li>
        <li><strong>Hand sanitizer stations:</strong> Now standard rather than optional</li>
        <li><strong>Visible cleaning protocols:</strong> More frequent servicing and "just cleaned" indicators</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="luxury-growth">Luxury Segment Expansion</h2>

      <p>The high-end portable restroom market is booming:</p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Wedding demand:</strong> Couples increasingly budget for luxury trailers as a priority item</li>
        <li><strong>Corporate events:</strong> Companies upgrading facilities to reflect brand standards</li>
        <li><strong>VIP experiences:</strong> Festivals offering premium restroom access as a ticket upgrade</li>
        <li><strong>New features:</strong> Bluetooth speakers, smartphone charging, premium toiletries</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="what-this-means">What This Means for You</h2>

      <h3>For Event Planners</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Book earlier than ever:</strong> 2-4 months ahead for standard events, longer for luxury</li>
        <li><strong>Budget for increases:</strong> Expect 10-20% higher costs than last year</li>
        <li><strong>Ask about eco options:</strong> Solar and green alternatives may be available</li>
        <li><strong>Prioritize hygiene features:</strong> Guests expect touchless and well-maintained facilities</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>For Construction Managers</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Secure long-term contracts:</strong> Lock in pricing for multi-month projects</li>
        <li><strong>Plan for lead times:</strong> Don't assume same-week delivery is available</li>
        <li><strong>Consider servicing frequency:</strong> More frequent cleaning may be expected by workers</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>For Homeowners</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Renovation planning:</strong> Factor in porta potty costs and book ahead</li>
        <li><strong>Party planning:</strong> Reserve units 3-4 weeks before your event</li>
        <li><strong>Compare quotes:</strong> Prices vary more than ever between providers</li>
      </ol>

    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="mt-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center border border-blue-100">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Ready to Book?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">Find trusted portable restroom providers and get quotes for 2025</p>
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center bg-primary-600 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-xl font-semibold hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors">
        Search Providers Near You
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Related -->
    <section class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Related Articles</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        {relatedPosts.map((related) => (
          <a href={`/blog/${related.slug}`} class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-gray-700">{related.category}</span>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-3 line-clamp-2">{related.title}</h3>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
